"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438166","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-22","<p>PCS representatives have requested to meet with me. I look forward to the meeting which will be organised in the New Year</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438166/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-22T22:24:31.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438166/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438166/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-14","Land Registry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will meet staff representatives in HM Land Registry to discuss concerns they have regarding the announcement in the Spending Review Autumn Statement 2015 which stated that the Government would be consulting on options to move operations of the Land Registry to the private sector from 2017.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","20023"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438167","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-22","<p>In the Spending Review Autumn Statement 2015 the Chancellor announced the Government’s intent to consult on options to move operations of the Land Registry into the private sector from 2017.</p><br /><p>We intend to launch the consultation in the New Year setting out Government’s proposals. Final decisions on the options to be included in the consultation have not yet been made.</p><br /><p>No decisions on the options will be taken until after the consultation, but, if Government chose to proceed we would look to then introduce any legislation required.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438167/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-22T15:03:50.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438167/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438167/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-14","Land Registry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, if he will publish the timetable for the proposed change of status of the Land Registry before a public consultation on that matter takes place; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","19851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438168","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-22","<p>Land Registry total revenue for 2014/15 was £297.1m. Land Registry paid a dividend of £19.1m to the Exchequer.</p><br /><p>As a Trading Fund, Land Registry is subject to government rules set out in Managing Public Money. This specifies that the charges it makes for its core statutory functions should cover its full costs, 3.5% to reflect the cost of capital used in providing services. As a Trading Fund, Land Registry is required to return the charge for cost of capital to the Consolidated Fund as a dividend. In 2014/15 this ordinary dividend was £19.1million.</p><br /><p>In 2014/15 Land Registry also paid a special dividend of £100million to the Exchequer. This reflected over-recovery from customers in previous years as a result of higher than forecast volume of transactions.</p><br /> <br /> <br />","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438168/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-22T15:17:44.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438168/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438168/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-14","Land Registry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how much the Exchequer received from the HM Land Registry trading fund in 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","19852"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438169","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-01-05","<br /><p>Reports from Quarter 2 2015 show that the customer satisfaction score from the customer satisfaction survey is currently 95%.</p><br /> <br /> <br /><p><strong></strong></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438169/answer",,,,,,"2016-01-05T16:49:02.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438169/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438169/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-14","Land Registry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what information he holds on the public satisfaction rating of HM Land Registry.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","19853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438170","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-22","<p>In the Spending Review Autumn Statement 2015 the Chancellor announced the Government’s intent to consult on options to move operations of the Land Registry into the private sector from 2017.</p><br /><p>We intend to launch the consultation in the New Year setting out Government’s proposals. Final decisions on the options to be included in the consultation have not yet been made.</p><br /><p>No decisions on the options will be taken until after the consultation, but, if Government chose to proceed we would look to then introduce any legislation required.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438170/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-22T15:02:23.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438170/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438170/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-14","Land Registry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, with reference to the Spending Review and Autumn Statement 2015, section 10.5, when he plans to launch the consultation on the future status of the Land Registry; and whether the status quo will be one of the options put forward in that consultation.","false","Biography information for Carolyn Harris","Swansea East","Carolyn Harris","19962"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438171","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-12-21","<p>My most recent discussion with the Secretary of State for Justice took place on 1 December. The Government was elected with a mandate to implement its manifesto commitment to replace Labour’s flawed Human Rights Act with a Bill of Rights. The Government believes this can be done in a way that is consistent with the provisions of the Belfast Agreement.</p><br />","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438171/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-21T11:26:18.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438171/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438171/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-12-14","Bill of Rights: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions she has had with the Secretary of State for Justice on the effect of the proposed British Bill of Rights on Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Stephen Pound","Ealing North","Stephen Pound","19870"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438172","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-18","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 30 November 2015 to Question 17417 to the hon. Member for East Londonderry (Mr Campbell). The Report of the Independent Reviewer of the Justice and Security (Northern Ireland) Act 2007 which contains the requested information is published annually. The next report will be published in January 2016.</p><br />","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438172/answer","Hansard_extract_on_Bomb_Disposal_-_Northern_Ireland[1].docx","Hansard_extract_on_Bomb_Disposal_-_Northern_Ireland[1].docx","17417 - QnA extract on NI Bomb Disposal","17417 - QnA extract on NI Bomb Disposal",,"2015-12-18T12:03:13.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438172/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438172/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-14","Armed Forces: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many times army technical officers have been deployed to incidents in Northern Ireland in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Stephen Pound","Ealing North","Stephen Pound","19871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438173","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-12-17","<p>The Prime Minister believes that the UK’s best future lies within a reformed European Union. He is focused on addressing the concerns of the people of the United Kingdom and is confident that the right agreement can be reached.</p><p>Northern Ireland Office Ministers meet regularly with Irish Government Ministers to discuss a range of issues and will continue to do so.</p><br />","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438173/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-17T13:41:35.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438173/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438173/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-12-14","UK Membership of EU: Republic of Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions she has had with the Irish government on the implications for relations between the UK and the Republic of Ireland of the UK voting to leave the EU in the EU referendum.","false","Biography information for Stephen Pound","Ealing North","Stephen Pound","19858"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438174","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-12-17","<p>The Prime Minister believes that the UK’s best future lies within a reformed European Union. He is focused on addressing the concerns of the people of the United Kingdom and is confident that the right agreement can be reached.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438174/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-17T13:43:03.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438174/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438174/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-12-14","UK Membership of EU: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what assessment she has made of the implications for Northern Ireland of the UK voting to leave the EU in the EU referendum.","false","Biography information for Stephen Pound","Ealing North","Stephen Pound","19859"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438175","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-21","<p>We have begun the detailed work to take forward the Type 26 Global Combat Ship and the new general purpose frigate programmes outlined in the White Paper 'National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015 (Cmd 9161)'. It is too early to say how many jobs will be sustained by these programmes.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438175/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-21T14:24:57.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438175/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438175/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-14","Shipbuilding: Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many shipbuilding jobs will be supported by the construction of each of the (a) eight Type 26 anti-submarine frigates that are scheduled to be ordered and (b) proposed five new frigates to be developed under the new light frigate programme.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","19855"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438176","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-12-22","<p>The UK is committed to maintaining and strengthening its economic and diplomatic engagement with the Commonwealth. The Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron) led a strong UK delegation to the Commonwealth Heads of Government meeting (CHOGM) in Malta in November. He announced funding for a number of initiatives including to help the Commonwealth’s small island states develop their maritime economies.</p><p>The UK pressed to ensure that trade issues were covered in the CHOGM communique. Commonwealth leaders agreed to advance global trade negotiations and in particular ratify the WTO Trade Facilitation Agreement.</p><p>I and The Minister for Trade and Investment, the right hon the Lord Maude of Horsham, took part in the Commonwealth Business <br>Forum in Malta. Lord Maude addressed the opening plenary on leveraging trade networks across the Commonwealth, and pushed for progress on free trade agreements to facilitate and increase trade between Commonwealth countries. He also held a number of bilateral meetings to discuss trade and investment opportunities. The UK continues to be a strong supporter of the Commonwealth Enterprise and Investment Council which organised the Business Forum and is expanding business networks across the Commonwealth.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438176/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-22T15:21:26.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438176/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438176/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-12-14","Commonwealth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps the Government is taking to promote trade and diplomatic connections with the Commonwealth.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","19945"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438177","Department for Education","false","2015-12-22","<p>The Department received representations from animal welfare groups about the inclusion of animal welfare in the science curriculum in response to the consultation on the new National Curriculum.</p><p>The new primary science curriculum, introduced from September 2014, focuses on the essential scientific knowledge that children need to be educated citizens. It teaches pupils about the requirements for animals to survive such as appropriate habitat, food, water and air. Personal, Social, Health and Economic (PSHE) education also provides opportunities for pupils to be taught about animal welfare and teachers are free to decide what further activities they offer on this topic.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438177/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-22T10:49:59.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438177/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438177/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-14","Animal Welfare: Curriculum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what discussions (a) she and (b) her Department have had with animal welfare organisations on the incorporation of animal welfare in the national curriculum.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","19842"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438178","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-12-16","<p>The Government’s proposals on the review of the animal licensing legislation will be made available shortly.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438178/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-16T13:28:19.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438178/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438178/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-12-14","Animals: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 25 November 2015 to Question 17199, when she will publish the outcome of her Department's review of animal licensing legislation; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","19861"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438179","Department of Health","false","2015-12-17","<br /><p>In the Hospital Episode Statistics data it is not possible to identify patients that attended accident and emergency with a diagnosis of dementia.</p><br /><p>The Health and Social Care Information Centre have provided a count of finished admission episodes (FAEs) where there was a primary diagnosis of dementia for the years 2012-13 to 2014-15. This is shown in Table A.</p><br /><p>Note that this is not a count of people as the same person may have had more than one admission episode within the same time period.</p><br /><p>Table A: Count of FAEs where there was a primary diagnosis of dementia for the years 2012-13 to 2014-15</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Sum of FAEs</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>19,274</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>17,939</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>18,732</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>Source: Hospital Episode Statistics (HES), Health and Social Care Information Centre</p><br /> <br /> <br />","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438179/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-17T14:01:28.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438179/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438179/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-14","Dementia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many patients with a diagnosis of dementia (a) attended A&E and (b) were admitted to hospital in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Debbie Abrahams","Oldham East and Saddleworth","Debbie Abrahams","20002"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438180","Department of Health","false","2016-01-05","<p>In line with previous requests of this nature, copies of communications on this issue are not proposed to be placed in the Library, as all communications from officials were for the purpose of providing advice to ministers for their consideration and deliberation. Releasing this information would be likely to inhibit the continued free and frank exchange of views for the purposes of deliberation.</p><br /><p>Based on clinical advice from the NHS England National Medical Director Sir Bruce Keogh, the Secretary of State agreed with the recommendation to standardise reporting arrangements. The recommendation came from Sir Bruce Keogh’s review of waiting time standards published in June 2015. The overall approach was agreed in September by the respective chief executives of NHS England, TDA and Monitor with the Secretary of State for Health.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438180/answer",,,,,,"2016-01-05T15:48:50.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438180/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438180/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-14","Health Services: Weather","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will place in the Library a copy of the communication between Ministers and officials in his Department about NHS England's decision to change the amount of NHS performance data published the Winter Daily Situation Reports for 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","20061"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438181","Department of Health","false","2016-01-05","<p>My Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State is generally accompanied by an official from the Department and/or a member of staff from his private office when he is travelling on official business.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438181/answer",,,,,,"2016-01-05T15:50:24.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438181/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438181/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-14","Department of Health: Visits Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, who he was accompanied by at a cost to the public purse on each of his official overseas trips since his appointment.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","19850"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438182","Department of Health","false","2016-01-05","<p>The NHS (General Medical Services - Premises Costs) Directions 2013 set out the circumstances under which NHS England may provide funding for general practitioner (GP) premises. NHS England does not provide funding for all refurbishments and replacements, and in some cases such works may be carried out by third party owners. As such neither the Department nor NHS England hold information on the number or proportion of GP premises that have been refurbished or replaced since May 2010.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438182/answer",,,,,,"2016-01-05T10:24:00.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438182/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/438182/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-12-14","GP Surgeries: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what information his Department or NHS England holds on the number and proportion of GP premises that have been refurbished or replaced since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Karin Smyth","Bristol South","Karin Smyth","19840"
