"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437078","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-20","<p>The staff figures (full-time equivalent) for 2010/11, 2012/13 and 2014/15 are set out below:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>FTE (Core BIS only, not UKTI)</strong></p></td><td><p><strong><em>Source/Notes</em></strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>2,781</p></td><td><p><em>Published in the BIS Annual Report &amp; Accounts 2011 (Core Dept (3,373) minus UKTI (592))</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>2,692</p></td><td><p><em>Published in the BIS Annual Report &amp; Accounts 2014/15 </em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>2,627</p></td><td><p><em>Published in the BIS Annual Report &amp; Accounts 2014/15 </em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><br></p></td><td><p><em></em></p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>In the further years of this Parliament, the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills (BIS) is expecting to make further headcount reductions in the core Department, in line with our Spending Review settlement and our efficiency programme ambitions. The exact figures for full time equivalents in these years are not available at this stage.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437078/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-20T07:44:20.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437078/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437078/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-10","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many staff by full-time equivalence there were in his Department in (a) 2010-11, (b) 2012-13 and (c) 2014-15; and how many staff by full-time equivalence he expects there will be in his Department in (i) 2015-16, (ii) 2016-17 and (iii) 2017-18.","false","Biography information for Gordon Marsden","Blackpool South","Gordon Marsden","19692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437079","Cabinet Office","false","2015-12-15","<p>The Cabinet Office will be working with the Office for National Statistics to consider ways to improve data collection capability, including potential legislative options.</p>","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437079/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-15T17:35:30.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437079/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437079/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-12-10","Self-employed: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will make representations to the Office for National Statistics to include earnings from self-employment in its weekly earnings series.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","19698"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437080","Cabinet Office","false","2015-12-15","<p><a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">GOV.UK</a> Verify is currently in public beta and is constantly being improved and expanded based on user feedback. Currently, 80% of the overall UK adult population can be assured. Other methods are available to ensure services are universally available.</p><p><a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">GOV.UK</a> Verify uses certified companies to check users. Each certified company performs checks before verifying your identity to <a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">GOV.UK</a> to meet assurance standards set by the Government. It is possible to verify your identity using a wide range of identity evidence, including any passport, any EU identity document, and any bank account or payment card.</p><br />","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437080/answer",,,,,"19584","2015-12-15T15:35:12.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437080/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437080/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-12-10","Proof of Identity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what proportion of the population can the Verify identity assurance system assure the identity of.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","19576"
