"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437082","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-15","<p>Information on the figures you have requested can be found in the publication, Child and Working Tax Credits statistics, finalised annual awards - geographical analysis, which is available at:</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-geographical-statistics-2013-to-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-geographical-statistics-2013-to-2014</a></p><p><br> <br> <br> Provisional information on the number of families in receipt of WTC is also available in the publication, Child and Working Tax Credits statistics – geographical analyses: April 2015, found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-and-working-tax-credits-statistics-provisional-awards-geographical-analyses-december-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-and-working-tax-credits-statistics-provisional-awards-geographical-analyses-december-2013</a></p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437082/answer",,,,,"19644","2015-12-15T17:35:23.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437082/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437082/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-10","Working Tax Credit: Salford and Eccles","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the average award of working tax credits is in Salford and Eccles constituency.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","19508"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437083","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-16","<br /><p>The Government takes the enforcement of National Minimum Wage very seriously.Any worker who believes that they are being paid below the minimum wage should make a complaint to the Acas helpline on 0300 123 1100. HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) reviews every complaint that is referred to them by the Acas helpline. Additionally, HMRC collate and analyse data from various sources in order to identify those employers who are potentially more likely to be underpaying National Minimum Wage, so that they can undertake targeted enforcement against those employers.</p><br /><p>For reasons of confidentiality, HMRC do not divulge information relating to the affairs of an individual or company or confirm whether or not there is an ongoing enquiry.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437083/answer",,,,,"19517","2015-12-16T16:34:03.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437083/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437083/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-10","Sports Direct: Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps his Department has taken to investigate whether employees of Sports Direct are paid the minimum wage.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","19516"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437084","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-16","<br /><p>The Government takes the enforcement of National Minimum Wage very seriously.Any worker who believes that they are being paid below the minimum wage should make a complaint to the Acas helpline on 0300 123 1100. HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) reviews every complaint that is referred to them by the Acas helpline. Additionally, HMRC collate and analyse data from various sources in order to identify those employers who are potentially more likely to be underpaying National Minimum Wage, so that they can undertake targeted enforcement against those employers.</p><br /><p>For reasons of confidentiality, HMRC do not divulge information relating to the affairs of an individual or company or confirm whether or not there is an ongoing enquiry.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437084/answer",,,,,"19516","2015-12-16T16:34:03.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437084/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437084/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-10","Sports Direct: Minimum Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if HM Revenue and Customs will investigate enforcement of the minimum wage at Sports Direct.","false","Biography information for Ian Austin","Dudley North","Ian Austin","19517"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437085","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-15","<p>This is a matter for the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), which is operationally independent from Government.</p><br /><p>This question has been passed on to the FCA. They will reply directly to the Honorable Member Helen Jones by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437085/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-15T13:08:35.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437085/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437085/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-10","Investment Trusts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what information the Financial Conduct Authority holds on (a) the reasons for which Mourant Fund Services Ltd did not complete its transaction to take over the operation of the Connaught Income Fund in 2009 and (b) whether at the time Mourant Fund Services Ltd was in possession of information about the Connaught Income Fund which should have been reported to the regulatory authorities.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","19565"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437086","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-15","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) has recruited 3,000 new staff into customer service roles this year. In particular, this has increased the number of people available on its telephone helplines outside normal office hours, when many customers choose to call.</p><p>HMRC has also undertaken its biggest-ever training programme as it seeks to build its customer support teams. This has included training 1,600 existing staff on a wider range of work to better meet customer demand.</p><br /><p>Average call waiting times have improved significantly. From April to June it was 19 mins; from July to September it was 13 mins; in November it was under 10 minutes.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437086/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-15T17:44:18.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437086/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437086/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-10","Revenue and Customs: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he is taking to reduce waiting times for the HMRC public service helpline.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","19566"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437087","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-15","<p>Household income inequality statistics are produced as part of the Office for National Statistics publication “The Effects of Taxes and Benefits on Household Income”, which can be found here:</p><p><a href="http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/household-income/the-effects-of-taxes-and-benefits-on-household-income/2013-2014/index.html" target="_blank">http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/household-income/the-effects-of-taxes-and-benefits-on-household-income/2013-2014/index.html</a></p><br />","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437087/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-15T16:07:05.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437087/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437087/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-10","Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to his Oral statement of 25 November 2015, Official Report, column 1369, on the Spending Review and Autumn Statement, what the evidential basis is for his statement that inequality is down.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","19555"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437088","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-15","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) takes a risk-based approach to employer compliance interventions, checking that employers and contractors have complied with their tax obligations. There are a variety of methods by which employers make payment to their employees, and HMRC will check wages have been received net of the appropriate tax and National Insurance Contributions deductions as part of our compliance intervention activity, regardless of the method of payment. Where this activity identifies that there may be non-compliance with other taxes, HMRC takes steps to address this risk.</p><br /><p>Where inaccuracies are found, HMRC will consider whether a penalty is appropriate based on the behaviour which led to the inaccuracy. The penalty will be highest in circumstances in which the behaviour which led to the inaccuracy was deliberate.</p><br /><p>HMRC is conducting research into the role of cash in facilitating non-compliance, and into the trends which are likely to change that role. As part of this work, on 25 November 2015 HMRC published a call for evidence on cash, tax evasion and the hidden economy, which seeks a better understanding of what implications the trend away from cash has for tax compliance.</p><br /><p>The call for evidence is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/cash-tax-evasion-and-the-hidden-economy-call-for-evidence" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/cash-tax-evasion-and-the-hidden-economy-call-for-evidence</a></p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437088/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-15T17:53:54.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437088/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437088/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-10","Pay: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps HM Revenue and Customs is talking to ensure that payroll taxes are collected from employers who pay wages in cash; what recent estimate he has made of the number of (a) employers using cash in hand for payroll and (b) employees receiving wages in cash; and what information he holds on the prevalence of payment of wages in cash in different sectors.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","19561"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437089","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-12-15","<p>The number of claimants in receipt of Pension Credit in Salford and Eccles constituency as at May 2015 is 4,750, of which 440 are also in receipt of the carer addition.</p><br /><p><strong>Source:</strong> DWP, 100% data.</p><br /><p>Notes:</p><ol><li>Figures are rounded to the nearest ten; some additional disclosure control has also been applied. May 2015 is the latest available data.</li><li><strong>STATE PENSION AGE:</strong> The age at which men and women reach State Pension age is gradually increasing. Under current legislation, State Pension age for women will equalise with State Pension age for men at 65 in 2018. Both men's and women's State Pension age will increase from 65 to 66 between December 2018 and October 2020. The Pensions Bill 2013-14 contains provision for a State Pension age of 67 to be reached by 2028. For more information see:</li></ol><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/207966/espa.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/207966/espa.pdf</a>.</p><ol start="3"><li><strong>Parliamentary Constituency of claimant (Westminster)</strong> these constituencies are used for the Westminster parliament.</li></ol><br />","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437089/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-15T17:25:57.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437089/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437089/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-12-10","Pensioners: Salford and Eccles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in Salford and Eccles constituency are in receipt of (a) pension credit and (b) the carer addition.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","19562"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437090","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-15","<p>It is the responsibility of engagers to determine the correct status of workers they engage. HM Revenue &amp; Customs have developed an Employment Status Indicator to help engagers: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/employment-status-indicator" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/guidance/employment-status-indicator</a></p><p>There is also further help with the status of lorry drivers: <a href="http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/Manuals/esmmanual/ESM4210.htm" target="_blank">www.hmrc.gov.uk/Manuals/esmmanual/ESM4210.htm</a></p><p>HM Revenue &amp; Customs is aware that false self-employment presents a tax risk and has deployed compliance resources to address that risk.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437090/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-15T17:52:57.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437090/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437090/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-10","Large Goods Vehicle Drivers: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that lorry drivers have the correct status for the purposes of tax payment.","true","Biography information for Robert Flello","Stoke-on-Trent South","Robert Flello","19551"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437091","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-16","<p>Air Passenger Duty is payable by airlines and not on a per airport basis. Therefore HMRC does not collect the data to produce a reliable estimate.</p><br /><p>The government is currently undertaking a consultation into options to support regional airports from the impacts of air passenger duty devolution. We are carefully considering the evidence we have received from stakeholders and will respond in due course.</p><br />","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437091/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-16T16:28:15.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437091/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437091/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-10","Air Passenger Duty","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate his Department has made of (a) the current proportion of air passenger duty revenues which are raised from Manchester Airport and (b) the potential effect on that proportion of air passenger duty in Scotland being reduced by 50 per cent.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","19572"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437092","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-15","<p>Reporting on asset sales is made on a financial year basis in departmental accounts. During the 2014-15 financial year the government received £4.2bn from sales of financial assets and £0.2bn from other commercial and financial assets. The timing of any further transactions is a commercial matter and the Government does not forecast exact timing of all sales within a particular fiscal year. Around £30bn of sales are expected in total during 2015-16.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437092/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-15T16:06:02.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437092/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437092/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-10","Government Departments: Assets","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what were the total receipts from the sale of Government assets (a) from 1 January to 7 May 2015 and (b) from 8 May 2015 to date; and whether any further such sales are expected to take place before the end of the calendar year.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","19580"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437093","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-15","<p>Information on the figures you have requested can be found in the publication, Child and Working Tax Credits statistics, finalised annual awards - geographical analysis, which is available at:</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-geographical-statistics-2013-to-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-geographical-statistics-2013-to-2014</a></p><p><br> <br> <br> Provisional information on the number of families in receipt of WTC is also available in the publication, Child and Working Tax Credits statistics – geographical analyses: April 2015, found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-and-working-tax-credits-statistics-provisional-awards-geographical-analyses-december-2013" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/child-and-working-tax-credits-statistics-provisional-awards-geographical-analyses-december-2013</a></p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437093/answer",,,,,"19508","2015-12-15T17:35:23.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437093/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437093/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-10","Working Tax Credit: Salford and Eccles","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many people in Salford and Eccles constituency are in receipt of working tax credits.","false","Biography information for Rebecca Long Bailey","Salford and Eccles","Rebecca Long Bailey","19644"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437094","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-17","<p>UK banks and building societies that participate in in the Funding for Lending Scheme (FLS) are able to borrow funding from the Bank of England, with the amount they are able to borrow (their ‘borrowing allowance’) linked to their net lending performance. FLS usage and lending data is published on the Bank of England website at the following link: http://www.bankofengland.co.uk/markets/Pages/FLS/extensiondata.aspx</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437094/answer",,,,,"19659 ; 19669","2015-12-17T12:31:28.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437094/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437094/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-10","Small Businesses: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much from the Funding for Lending scheme has been lent to small and medium-sized enterprises in (a) Scotland and (b) Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill constituency.","false","Biography information for Philip Boswell","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Phil Boswell","19670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437095","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-17","<p>The Bank of England does not lend directly to small and medium sized enterprises as part of the Funding for Lending Scheme (FLS). Under the FLS, the Bank of England provides funding to UK banks and building societies participating in the scheme. The amount of funding participant banks and building societies are eligible to borrow from the Bank of England is determined by their net lending to certain sectors of the economy.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437095/answer",,,,,"19664 ; 19668","2015-12-17T14:15:28.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437095/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437095/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-10","Small Businesses: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what statistical information his Department holds on small- and medium-sized enterprises which have defaulted on a loan received through the Funding for Lending Scheme.","false","Biography information for Philip Boswell","Coatbridge, Chryston and Bellshill","Phil Boswell","19662"
