"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437100","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-15","<p>A full list of external research reports commissioned by HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC), with links to the full reports, is published on the HMRC website here:</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hm-revenue-and-customs-research-report-collection" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hm-revenue-and-customs-research-report-collection</a></p><br />","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437100/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-15T17:38:15.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437100/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437100/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-10","Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to paragraph 4.2 of the Government response to the 49th Report from the Committee of Public Accounts, Session 2014-15, for the effective management of tax reliefs, if he will (a) list and (b) place in the Library the external research reports commissioned by his Department which covers the use of tax reliefs.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","19632"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437101","HM Treasury","false","2015-12-16","<p>The UK is supportive of Commission action against illegal state aid, including recovery where illegal state aid has been found. This is an important part of ensuring that the single market works effectively and on the basis of fair competition.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437101/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-16T16:29:21.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437101/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437101/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-12-10","Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with the EU Commissioner on Competition on plans for recovering unpaid taxes and preventing multinationals avoiding tax.","false","Biography information for Richard Arkless","Dumfries and Galloway","Richard  Arkless","19684"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437102","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-12-17","<p>The Department does not hold information centrally on the amount or type of land held by community land trusts.</p><p>The Department’s annual Green Belt statistics monitor the amount of land designated as Green Belt in England and any changes to the designated area since the previous year. The statistics record the change by local planning authority.</p><p>Of the local planning authorities for which information was requested, the following have made changes to the Green Belt in the last five years:</p><p>East Dorset reduced the area of designated Green Belt in 2014-15 by 160 hectares to 16,720 hectares, a reduction of 1 per cent; and</p><p>Purbeck increased the area of designated Green Belt in 2012-13 by 460 hectares to 8,200 hectares, an increase of 6 per cent.</p><br />","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437102/answer",,,,,"19604 ; 19609 ; 19610 ; 19611 ; 19612 ; 19613 ; 19614 ; 19615 ; 19616 ; 19679 ; 19680 ; 19681 ; 19683","2015-12-17T15:54:56.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437102/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/437102/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-12-10","Green Belt: Dorset","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what proportion of green belt land in the Poole Unitary Authority area has been redesignated in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Michael Tomlinson","Mid Dorset and North Poole","Michael Tomlinson","19682"
